# cn() Utility

## Setup
```bash
npm install clsx tailwind-merge
```

```ts
// lib/utils.ts (auto-generated by shadcn init)
import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';
import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';

export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {
  return twMerge(clsx(inputs));
}
```

## Usage Patterns
```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

// Conditional classes
<div className={cn('base-class', isActive && 'active-class', isError && 'text-red-500')} />

// Variant-based component
interface CardProps {
  className?: string;
  variant?: 'default' | 'elevated';
}

function Card({ className, variant = 'default', ...props }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <div
      className={cn(
        'rounded-lg border bg-card p-4',
        variant === 'elevated' && 'shadow-lg',
        className  // consumer overrides come last
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}

// Merges conflicts correctly:
cn('p-4 p-2')           // → 'p-2'
cn('text-red-500', 'text-blue-500')  // → 'text-blue-500'
```

## Why twMerge matters
Without `tailwind-merge`, `clsx('p-4', 'p-2')` → `'p-4 p-2'` (both applied, last wins in CSS but confusing). With merge → `'p-2'` (intentional).

# Tailwind CSS v4

## Installation
```bash
npm install tailwindcss@next @tailwindcss/vite
# or for Next.js:
npm install tailwindcss@next @tailwindcss/postcss
```

## CSS-First Configuration (replaces tailwind.config.js)
```css
/* app/globals.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-brand: oklch(65% 0.2 250);
  --color-brand-foreground: oklch(98% 0 0);

  --font-sans: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;

  --radius-sm: 0.375rem;
  --radius-md: 0.5rem;
  --radius-lg: 0.75rem;

  --spacing-18: 4.5rem;
}
```

## New Utility Patterns
```html
<!-- Dynamic values without arbitrary syntax -->
<div class="grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fill,minmax(280px,1fr))]">...</div>

<!-- CSS variables as utilities -->
<div class="text-[--color-brand]">...</div>

<!-- Container queries (native in v4) -->
<div class="@container">
  <div class="@md:flex-row flex flex-col">...</div>
</div>

<!-- Logical properties -->
<div class="ms-4 me-2 ps-6">...</div>

<!-- New color syntax -->
<div class="bg-blue-500/80">80% opacity blue</div>
```

## Vite Plugin (v4 preferred)
```ts
// vite.config.ts
import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite';

export default { plugins: [tailwindcss()] };
```

## v3 → v4 Key Differences
- `tailwind.config.js` → `@theme {}` in CSS
- `content` array → auto-detection
- `@apply` still works but `@theme` preferred
- `ring-offset-*` → integrated into `ring-*`

